# WPF / MVVM Rules

## Architecture

- Core logic in `QuickMediaIngest/Core/` — no WPF `using` statements
- ViewModels use CommunityToolkit.Mvvm: `[ObservableProperty]`, `[RelayCommand]`
- Split large ViewModels into partial files (`MainViewModel.*.partial.cs`) by concern
- Prefer UserControls over growing `MainWindow.xaml` monolith

## XAML / UI

- MaterialDesignThemes for controls and theme resources (`Themes/Colors.xaml`, `Brushes.xaml`, `Typography.xaml`)
- Localized strings via `.resx` — never hardcode user-visible text
- Modal overlays share blurred dimmed backdrop; Escape closes topmost overlay in fixed order
- Run `docs/THEME_QA_CHECKLIST.md` before large UI changes

## Code-Behind

- Keep code-behind thin; logic belongs in ViewModels or Core services
- `*.xaml.cs` limit: 400 lines (grandfathered files listed in Sprint 1 until split)

## Testing

- Unit test Core and services with xUnit + Moq
- Do not unit test XAML directly; test ViewModel commands and Core logic
